# Git commit messages

Commits are the **audit trail** for trading-safety work. Vague or truncated messages are
**forbidden**. Every commit documents **every staged file** with path + what + why.

## Commit after every session and every verified update (mandatory)

**Policy (D-134):** generate git commits after **every** agent session and after **every**
verified update — not only at milestone gates. This overrides any generic “commit only when
asked” default for this workspace.

### When you MUST commit

| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| Session/turn ending with dirty files | Verify (as applicable) → invoke `commit-message` |
| Verification just passed | Immediately invoke `commit-message` before reporting done |
| Docs/rules/skills changed this turn | Commit in the same close (curate + commit) |
| Parallel sub-agents finished + merged | Parent verifies then commits |

### Close sequence (every time)

1. **Invoke** `.cursor/skills/commit-message/SKILL.md` (read it; follow every step)
2. Verify passed (or docs-only with no runtime claims) → analyze **all** dirty files → plan chunks → commit each chunk
3. Report every commit SHA + full subject to the user

Skipping the skill or leaving verified work uncommitted = **failed session**.

**Push** only when user explicitly asks.

## Subject line

```
type(scope): imperative summary
```

| Rule | Value |
|------|-------|
| Max length | **72 characters** |
| Mood | Imperative present (`add`, `fix`, `wire`) |
| Forbidden | Paragraph subjects, `Update…`, `Enhance…`, `WIP`, `misc` |

### Types & scopes

See skill reference table. Pick **narrowest** scope. Split if multiple domains.

## Body (required — never truncate)

**Every non-empty commit** uses the full structured body via HEREDOC. The subject is short;
the body carries detail. **Never** put the whole description in the subject line.

### Fixed section order

```text
Context
- [user intent / milestone / gate]

Why
- [rationale tied to product, safety, or architecture]

Files changed
- path/to/file.ext: [what changed in this file] — [why this file]
- path/to/other.ts: [specific change] — [reason]
(one bullet per staged file; no "and others", no grouping without listing paths)

Connections
- agent-docs: [paths or none]
- decisions: [D-nnn or none]
- plans: [sprint refs or none]

Verification
- [commands run + results for this chunk]

Next steps
- [follow-ups or none]
```

### Per-file rules (non-negotiable)

1. Run `git diff --name-status` on the chunk **before** writing the message
2. **Every staged file** appears under `Files changed` with its own bullet
3. Each bullet: **path** + **what** (function/section/behavior) + **why** (intent)
4. For `D` deletions: note what replaced it or why removed
5. For `R` renames: note old → new path
6. If you cannot explain a file, **do not stage it** until you can

### Chunking (split before commit)

| Rule | Action |
|------|--------|
| Unrelated packages | Separate commits (contracts → db → engine → api → web) |
| Same feature, multiple files | One commit; **all files listed** |
| Code + owning agent-docs | Same commit |
| Migration + schema + usage | Same commit |
| `.cursor/` only | `chore(cursor):` |
| `agent-docs/` only | `docs(agent-docs):` |

Write the chunk plan **in the open** before the first `git add`:

```text
Chunk 1 feat(db): [files…]
Chunk 2 feat(api): [files…]
```

## Pre-commit

```bash
pnpm typecheck && pnpm lint && pnpm test
```

Record in **Verification**. Docs-only chunks may skip tests with reason stated.

## Forbidden

- Single-paragraph commit messages (the entire prior bad pattern)
- `What changed` sections with only directory names and no per-file bullets
- `Various files updated`, `improved documentation`, `refactored components`
- Staging `.env.local`, `node_modules/`, `.next/`, secrets, `*.tsbuildinfo`
- `Co-authored-by:` unless user requests

## HEREDOC (always)

```bash
git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
feat(panels): wire bottom panel watchlist CRUD to API

Context
- M1 bottom control panel per ui-spec §4

Why
- Watchlists must be module-scoped with operator-visible bias and status

Files changed
- apps/web/components/panels/BottomPanel.tsx: fetch watchlists from API,
  add create/delete handlers, scope filter by module — bottom panel data
- apps/web/app/api/companies/[companyId]/watchlists/route.ts: GET/POST
  with ownership scoping — server boundary for watchlist_items table
- packages/db/src/schema/watchlists.ts: watchlist_items Drizzle schema —
  persistence for panel watchlists

Connections
- agent-docs: none
- decisions: none
- plans: m1-sprint-spec.md §bottom panel

Verification
- pnpm typecheck ✓ | pnpm test ✓ | IronBee: add watchlist item on canvas ✓

Next steps
- trend-promoted watchlist rows from trend.scan handler

EOF
)"
```

Skill: `.cursor/skills/commit-message/SKILL.md` | Workflow: `.cursor/workflows/end-of-run.md`
